63年","1318–1376":"1318年–1376年","1316–1341":"1316年–1341年","1340–1405":"1340年–1405年","1290–1363":"1290年–1363年","1292–1363":"1292年–1363年","1341":"1341年","1363":"1363年","1340":"1340年","1292":"1292年","1290":"1290年","1316":"1316年","1337":"1337年","1315":"1315年","1314":"1314年","1332":"1332年","1376":"1376年","1453":"1453年","1309":"1309年","1318":"1318年","1328":"1328年","1317":"1317年","1405":"1405年","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"英国英格兰武斯特斯爾斯特倫善姆","lifeSummary":"当Robert Russell于1314年出生在英国武斯特斯爾斯特倫善姆时，他的父亲John Russell25岁，母亲Elizabeth FitzEllis23岁。他于1332年与Katherine Vampage在英国英格兰武斯特斯爾斯特倫善姆结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1376年在英国英格兰武斯特斯爾斯特倫善姆享年62岁，埋葬在英国武斯特斯爾斯特倫善姆。"},"hr":{"1314–1376":"1314.–1376.","1309–Male":"1309.–preminuo","1315–1363":"1315–1363.","1318–1376":"1318–1376.","1316–1341":"1316–1341.","1340–1405":"1340.–1405","1290–1363":"1290–1363.","1292–1363":"1292–1363.","1341":"1341.","1363":"1363.","1340":"1340.","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1314":"1314.","1332":"1332.","1376":"1376.","1453":"1453","1309":"1309.","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1405":"1405","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1314–1376":"1314–1376","1309–Male":"1309–Zesnulý","1315–1363":"1315–1363","1318–1376":"1318–1376","1316–1341":"1316–1341","1340–1405":"1340–1405","1290–1363":"1290–1363","1292–1363":"1292–1363","1341":"1341","1363":"1363","1340":"1340","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1314":"1314","1332":"1332","1376":"1376","1453":"1453","1309":"1309","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1405":"1405","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1314–1376":"1314–1376","1309–Male":"1309–Afdød","1315–1363":"1315–1363","1318–1376":"1318–1376","1316–1341":"1316–1341","1340–1405":"1340–1405","1290–1363":"1290–1363","1292–1363":"1292–1363","1341":"1341","1363":"1363","1340":"1340","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1314":"1314","1332":"1332","1376":"1376","1453":"1453","1309":"1309","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1405":"1405","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1314–1376":"1314–1376","1309–Male":"1309–Overleden","1315–1363":"1315–1363","1318–1376":"1318–1376","1316–1341":"1316–1341","1340–1405":"1340–1405","1290–1363":"1290–1363","1292–1363":"1292–1363","1341":"1341","1363":"1363","1340":"1340","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1314":"1314","1332":"1332","1376":"1376","1453":"1453","1309":"1309","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1405":"1405","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1314–1376":"1314–1376","1309–Male":"1309–Deceased","1315–1363":"1315–1363","1318–1376":"1318–1376","1316–1341":"1316–1341","1340–1405":"1340–1405","1290–1363":"1290–1363","1292–1363":"1292–1363","1341":"1341","1363":"1363","1340":"1340","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1314":"1314","1332":"1332","1376":"1376","1453":"1453","1309":"1309","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1405":"1405","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Russell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: of Norman origin, from Old French and Anglo-Norman French <i>r(o)ussel</i>, a diminutive of Old French <i>rous(e)</i> ‘red, reddish’, used either as a nickname for someone with red hair or a ruddy complexion, or as a personal name. Compare   Rouse  . This Norman name has been established in Ireland since the 12th century. It has been reinforced in Britain and Ireland by Huguenot bearers of the name <i>Roussel</i>, of the same Old French origin.","English: habitational name from any of several places called Rushall (Norfolk, Staffordshire, Wiltshire) or possibly sometimes from Rusthall in Speldhurst (Kent). Rushall in Staffordshire derives from Old English <i>rysc</i> ‘rush, rushes’ + <i>halh</i> ‘nook, corner of land’. Rushall in Norfolk derives from an uncertain first element + Old English <i>halh</i>. Rushall in Wiltshire derives from an Old English personal name <i>Rust</i> (genitive <i>Rustes</i>) + <i>halh</i>. Rusthall in Speldhurst (Kent) probably derives from Old English <i>rust</i> ‘rust, rust color’ + <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’, but with a change in the final element due to influence from Middle English, Old English <i>hall</i> ‘hall, residence’, perhaps referring to a nearby building.","Americanized form of German <b>Rüssel</b>, from a pet form of any of various personal names formed with the element <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame, renown’."],"variants":[{"name":"Russler","meanings":["German (<b>Rüssler</b>):","occupational name for a farmer, from an agent derivative of <i>rüsseln</i> ‘to shallow plow’.","variant of <b>Rüssel</b> (see   Russell   2)."]},{"name":"Rouse","meanings":["English: nickname for a person with red hair or a ruddy complexion, from Middle English, Anglo-Norman French <i>rous(e)</i> ‘red(-haired)’ (from Latin <i>russ(e)us</i>).","Americanized form of German   Raus  .","Walloon and northern French (<b>Rousé</b>): variant of <b>Rosé</b> (see   Rose  )."]},{"name":"Russel","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Russell  .","German: from a pet form of <i>Russ</i>, see   Russ   2.","northwest German (<b>Rüssel</b>): probably a variant of   Rossel  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":1,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":14,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":23,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Russell was born in 1314, in Strensham, Worcestershire, England, his father, John Russell, was 25 and his mother, Elizabeth FitzEllis, was 23. He married Katherine Vampage in 1332, in Strensham, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1376, in Strensham, Worcestersh